A User who wishes to login is presented with a login form, with two fields email and password. This is where login authentication comes into play, and the inputs of the user are checked against the database and id they values are correct they are logged in as there accounts user type (Customer Or Admin). Using @Security.Authenticated(Secured.class) verifies that a user is logged in before giving access to restricted commands. The AdminController is restricted to users of type Admin, they have the ability to add, update and delete. 
The Admin views the products through using the Products method in the home controller in a view, which is done by using the Chooses to edit a product, the user is presented with a form to edit the values of that product (updateProduct Method). They are shown a checkbox for the category of the product, where they can select multiple categories. They then hit save and the product has been updated.

